<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
2</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Why do the heathen rage, and the people imagine a vain thing?</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>The kings of the earth set      
themselves, and the rulers take counsel together, against YHVH, and against his 
MASHIYACH, saying,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>Let us break their bands asunder, and cast away their cords from us.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>He that sitteth   
in the heavens shall laugh: the ADONAY shall have them in derision.</P></TD>    
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Then shall he speak    
unto them in his wrath, and vex them in his sore displeasure.</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Yet have I set my king upon my  
holy hill of Zion.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>I will declare the decree: YHVH hath said unto me, Thou art my Son; this 
day have I begotten thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>Ask of me, and I shall give thee the heathen for thine inheritance, 
and the uttermost parts of the earth for thy possession.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou shalt break them with a rod of 
iron; thou shalt dash them in pieces like a potter's vessel.</P></TD></TR><TR>  
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>Be wise now therefore, O ye   
kings: be instructed, ye judges of the earth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>  
<A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>Serve YHVH with fear, and rejoice with       
trembling.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>  
Kiss the Son, lest he be angry, and ye perish from the way, when his wrath is   
kindled but a little. Blessed are all they that put their trust in him.</P></TD>
